  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group for financial intelligence units\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Customer due diligence procedures\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n- Reporting of suspicious financial activities\n- International information sharing\n- Significant financial penalties for non-compliance\n\n4. Typical Regulatory Approaches:\n- Mandatory background checks\n- Record-keeping requirements\n- Reporting large cash transactions\n- Implementing risk-based compliance programs\n\n5. Penalties:\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential business license revocation\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities across different financial sectors and jurisdictions.",
